OL,3,CUrban councils outside London warn
OL,4,CAngela Rayner of financial failure
OL,6,FIn a letter to the Deputy Prime
OL,7,FMinister ahead of the Labour Party
OL,8,Fconference this weekend, the Labour
OL,9,Fchairman of the Special Interest Group
OL,10,Fof Municipal Authorities (Sigoma), Sir
OL,11,FStephen Houghton, called for urgent
OL,12,FGovernment action to stabilise council
OL,13,Ffinances and clarity on the timing of
OL,14,Fpromised reforms.
OL,16,FA survey of finance directors at
OL,17,Fmember councils found just 3% are now
OL,18,Fvery confident they can balance the
OL,19,Fbooks in 2025-26, while just over one
OL,20,Fin five (21%) are not very confident
OL,21,Fthis will be the case.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
