OL,4,CAngela Rayner of financial failure
OL,6,FConfidence in adult social care
OL,7,Fdelivery is also low, with 65% of
OL,8,Fcouncils saying required standards
OL,9,Fcould not be maintained and 18%
OL,10,Fwarning of service failure.
OL,12,FThe high cost of placements, the vast
OL,13,Fmajority of which are provided by
OL,14,Fprivate companies, was identified by
OL,15,Ffinance directors as causing the most
OL,16,Facute pressure on social care budgets.
