OL,3,CUrban councils outside London warn
OL,4,CAngela Rayner of financial failure
OL,6,FSigoma, whose members include
OL,7,FManchester, Liverpool and Nottingham,
OL,8,Fhas repeatedly called for reform to
OL,9,Fthe way local government funding is
OL,10,Fdistributed to compensate poorer areas
OL,11,Fwhich are able to generate less
OL,12,Frevenue from council tax.
OL,14,FThe issue has become particularly
OL,15,Fpressing as local authorities have
OL,16,Fbecome increasingly reliant on the
OL,17,Flevy as annual central government
OL,18,Ffunding has reduced.
